description: Best known for an everyman persona that powered two classic TV sitcoms, Newhart managed to be the funniest guy in the room while playing unassuming characters.
title: 'I've lived in an incredible time': Comic Bob Newhart dies at 94

description: Michail Chkhikvishvili, an alleged leader of an extremist group called the Maniac Murder Cult, outlined a detailed plan to hand out poisoned candy to Jewish children and also target racial minorities.
title: A neo-Nazi leader is indicted for a plot to have a Santa Claus poison children in NYC

description: Top Democrats in Washington are mired in crisis over President Biden's continued candidacy — exacerbated by his COVID diagnosis. Biden has said he expects to be the party's nominee and is undeterred.
title: Top Democrats in Washington walking a careful line on Biden amid party panic about his candidacy

description: The two veteran rappers read as comic inversions of one another on their new albums, by turns renewed and restrained by the instincts that defined them at the start of their careers.
title: Eminem and Common confront the same milestone — middle age — from opposite angles

description: Nicolas Cage plays a satanic murderer, and Maika Monroe is the clairvoyant FBI agent on his trail, in this tense and frightening horror movie.
title: 'Longlegs' is a terrifying serial killer — who never touches his victims

description: Mateo Askaripour's sophomore novel is a sprawling speculative-fiction narrative that delivers a heartwarming story about a young woman learning to navigate the world.
title: 'This Great Hemisphere' tackles racism, classism, and political power struggles

description: Ukraine's bookstores have expanded despite the war, fueled by interest in works by Ukrainian writers, some who have been killed by Russian forces. But a Russian missile struck a top printing plant.
title: Ukraine's bookstores are thriving, but a top printing plant took a deadly hit

description: On Wednesday night at the Republican National Convention in Milwaukee, the Ohio senator toned down his usual rhetoric and focused instead on his family and his appeal to working-class voters.
title: Takeaways from J.D. Vance’s first date with America

description: In an era when connecting the tidbits of an artist’s private life can seem more important than following a musical thread between songs, West of Roan's Queen of Eyes revives faith in the power of the concept album.
title: West of Roan collects ancient folktales — not personal folklore

description: The blast that happened at the Port Chicago Naval Magazine in California killed 320 people and injured 400 more.
title: The Navy exonerates 256 Black sailors unjustly punished over 1944 WWII port explosion
